ğŸ”¹ STEP 1: Install Git (Ubuntu)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install git -y


Verify:

git --version

ğŸ”¹ STEP 2: Configure Git (ONE TIME)
git config --global user.name "YourGitHubUsername"
git config --global user.email "yourmail@gmail.com"


Check:

git config --list

ğŸ”¹ STEP 3: Create Project Folder & Initialize Git
mkdir myproject
cd myproject
git init


âœ” Git repository initialized

ğŸ”¹ STEP 4: Create a File & Check Status
echo "This is my first file" > testfile.txt
ls
git status

ğŸ”¹ STEP 5: Add File to Staging Area
git add testfile.txt


or add all files:

git add .

ğŸ”¹ STEP 6: Commit Changes
git commit -m "Added testfile"

ğŸ”¹ STEP 7: Create GitHub Repository

Go to GitHub

Click New Repository

Copy repository URL
Example:

https://github.com/username/myproject.git

ğŸ”¹ STEP 8: Connect Local Repo to GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/myproject.git


Verify:

git remote -v

ğŸ”¹ STEP 9: Push Code to GitHub (MAIN BRANCH)
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main

âœ… BRANCHING (VERY IMPORTANT FOR EXAM)
ğŸ”¹ STEP 10: Create New Branch
git checkout -b mybranch

ğŸ”¹ STEP 11: Add File in New Branch
echo "This is second file" > secondfile.txt
git add .
git commit -m "Added second file in mybranch"
git push -u origin mybranch

ğŸ”¹ STEP 12: Merge Branch into Main
git checkout main
git merge mybranch
git push

âœ… FOLDER & MULTIPLE FILES (From your notes)
mkdir notes syllabus
touch notes/readme.txt syllabus/readme.txt
git add .
git commit -m "Added notes and syllabus folders"
git push

âœ… IMPORTANT GIT COMMANDS (EXAM READY)
Purpose	Command
Check status	git status
View branches	git branch
Switch branch	git checkout branchname
Create branch	git checkout -b branchname
Merge branch	git merge branchname
Push code	git push
Pull code	git pull
